# Ventium SoC peripheral placement — where each device lives:
#   rtl = synthesized into the PL fabric (a ven_* RTL module in ventium_soc)
#   ps  = run as a C model on the PS A53 (the SoC forwards that port range over the
#         AXI-Lite io-bridge; ven_soc_axil + sw/ps_periph/<dev>.c service it)
#
# This is the fabric-fit knob: the KV260 PL is routing/congestion-bound, so push the
# SLOW peripherals onto the A53 and keep only the BUS-CRITICAL ones in PL. Run
#   python3 fpga/scripts/gen_periph_split.py
# to regenerate rtl/soc/ven_periph_split.svh (the +define gating) and the TB/PS
# C dispatch table (verif/tb/ps_periph_table.inc) from this file.
#
# Each `ps` device must have a matching C model in sw/ps_periph/<dev>.c, verified
# bit-exact vs qemu by run-soc-<dev>-gate.sh built with +VEN_<DEV>_PS (the device
# is then served by its C model instead of the RTL module).
#
#   device   placement   notes
# ---------- ---------   ----------------------------------------------------------
pic          rtl         # 8259 PIC      — bus-critical (INTR/INTA latency): keep in PL
pit          rtl         # 8254 PIT      — IRQ0 timebase: keep in PL
port92       rtl         # fast A20      — gates the address bus: keep in PL
ide          rtl         # IDE/ATA       — bus-master DMA path: keep in PL
dma          rtl         # 8237 ctrl0    — bus master: keep in PL
dma2         rtl         # 8237 ctrl1    — bus master: keep in PL
uart         ps          # 16550 COM1    — slow serial: A53 (C model present + verified)
# --- roadmap: the remaining SLOW peripherals move to PS as their C model lands
# --- (sw/ps_periph/<model>.c, verified bit-exact by run-soc-<dev>-gate +VEN_<DEV>_PS).
rtc          rtl         # MC146818 RTC  — slow, host-clock  -> PS once ven_rtc.c lands
i8042        rtl         # 8042 kbd/mouse— slow, host-queue  -> PS once ven_i8042.c lands
vga          rtl         # VGA registers — slow (+ PS scan-out) -> PS once ven_vgaregs.c lands
acpipm       rtl         # ACPI PM timer — slow              -> PS once ven_acpipm.c lands
fdc          rtl         # 82077 floppy  — slow command-FIFO -> PS once ven_i8272.c lands
